# Commit Message Guidelines

## Commit Message Format
- Keep commit messages SHORT and concise
- Follow Conventional Commits format: `<type>[optional scope]: <description>`
- Maximum length: ~50-60 characters for the subject line
- Do NOT include detailed bullet points or long descriptions in commit messages

## Changelog Documentation
- All detailed information about changes should be added to `CHANGELOG.md` as bullet points
- When committing, add detailed change information to CHANGELOG.md under the appropriate section
- Use bullet points format in CHANGELOG.md for clarity
- Keep CHANGELOG.md entries organized by type (Added, Changed, Fixed, Removed, etc.)

## Example
**Commit message (short):**
```
chore: update dependencies and increment versions in pubspec.yaml
```

**CHANGELOG.md entry (detailed):**
```markdown
### Changed
- Updated dependencies and incremented versions in pubspec.yaml
  - Updated flutter_svg to latest version
  - Updated image_picker to latest version
  - Updated firebase_messaging to latest version
  - ... (more details)
```

## Rule Summary
- ✅ Short commit messages (50-60 chars max)
- ✅ Detailed information goes to CHANGELOG.md
- ✅ Use bullet points in CHANGELOG.md
- ❌ No long descriptions in commit messages
- ❌ No bullet points in commit messages

